---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "GE Profile Refrigerator Repair | Southern California | French Door";
const description = "GE Profile refrigerator repair across Southern California, French Door, Counter-Depth, Full-Width Freezer Drawer, SmartHQ. Haier-owned mid-premium. $89 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/ge-profile-refrigerator-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is GE Profile the same as regular GE? We can't tell from the store.",
    a: "Different tier, same family. GE Profile is the feature-focused mid-premium tier of the GE Appliances brand family, positioned between base GE (value tier, $700–$2,000 range) and GE Café (style-first premium, $2,500–$8,000). GE Profile runs roughly $1,500–$5,000 and emphasizes feature richness, Counter-Depth French Door, Full-Width Freezer Drawer, SmartHQ Wi-Fi integration, advanced dispenser systems, without the style-forward aesthetic or luxury-tier pricing of GE Café or the built-in architecture of GE Monogram. Model number prefixes differentiate: PWE, PFE, PVD on Profile; CWE, CFE, CVE on Café; ZIR, ZIS on Monogram. All three are GE Appliances (Haier-owned since 2016), US-manufactured primarily at Appliance Park in Louisville, KY, with shared underlying refrigeration platforms but different feature sets, trim hardware, and electronics sophistication."
  },
  {
    q: "The Full-Width Freezer Drawer on our GE Profile, what's unique about it?",
    a: "The Full-Width Freezer Drawer is a GE Profile signature feature, a single-width drawer (as opposed to split twin-drawer architectures or hinged-door freezers) on the bottom of the French Door configuration. Advantages: easier loading, fewer hinges to maintain, and the freezer compartment appears more organized because you can lay items flat rather than stacking. Service implications: drawer-slide hardware carries more weight than a split drawer would, so slide wear at 6–10 years is something we see. Drawer-alignment adjustments if the drawer doesn't close flush are another service item. The freezer refrigeration cycle is conventional (single-evap behind the freezer compartment, not TwinChill dual-evap like Monogram), defrost cycle, fan, and heater service patterns mirror mainstream French Door architectures. Drawer-slide service $260–$440."
  },
  {
    q: "SmartHQ Wi-Fi, how critical is it for service, and does it fail?",
    a: "Helpful but not mission-critical. SmartHQ is GE Appliances' Wi-Fi platform across Profile, Café, and Monogram, enables status monitoring, setpoint adjustment, notification alerts, and OTA firmware updates via the GE SmartHQ app. When SmartHQ faults on a GE Profile refrigerator (Wi-Fi association drops, notifications don't deliver, app shows appliance offline), it's almost always either a router-side issue (check home Wi-Fi first) or a firmware revision on the appliance control board. We run SmartHQ diagnostic through the GE service interface, update firmware if available, replace Wi-Fi module only if firmware doesn't resolve the issue. The refrigeration cycle itself doesn't depend on SmartHQ connectivity, the fridge cools correctly whether Wi-Fi is working or not. Firmware update $120–$180; Wi-Fi module replacement $220–$360."
  },
  {
    q: "We have a GE Profile French Door, how long should the compressor realistically last?",
    a: "Field data from our LA coverage suggests 10–14 years of reliable service on GE Profile compressors with normal use, assuming no installation-specific issues (venting clearance, ambient-temperature excursions). The GE Profile compressor platform is the standard inverter-driven variable-speed architecture shared across much of the GE Appliances residential lineup. Post-warranty compressor replacement runs $900–$1,500 depending on SKU and refrigerant, lower than the luxury-tier brands because the platform is higher-volume and parts are widely available through GE's US distribution. For a 12-year-old GE Profile with a compressor fault, the repair-vs-replace math usually favors repair if the rest of the unit is in good shape; for 15-plus year units we walk through the honest calculation with current replacement cost against the compressor job."
  },
  {
    q: "Does the GE Profile water filter need professional replacement or can we do it ourselves?",
    a: "Homeowner-installable in almost all cases. GE Profile refrigerators use genuine GE-branded water filters (XWF, XWFE, RPWFE are the common current filters depending on model) that twist or slide into a filter housing inside the refrigerator. Replacement is a 2-minute operation, twist the old filter out, twist the new one in, run a water-flush cycle to purge air. Filters are available at most hardware stores, appliance parts stores, and directly from GE Appliances. Standard replacement interval is 6 months or when the filter-change indicator light activates (usually based on water-use volume, varies by household). Only call us for filter-related service if: the filter housing is damaged, the water pressure at the dispenser is low even with a fresh filter (indicates a fill-valve or reservoir issue), or if the filter light won't reset after replacement (electronic fault). Standard filter replacement is not a service call; housing or electronics service $180–$280."
  },
  {
    q: "Convertible Drawer on newer GE Profile models, does it work well?",
    a: "Yes, and it's one of the more interesting features in the Profile lineup. Convertible Drawer is a compartment (typically sized like a Perfect Temp-style full-width drawer) that switches between 5 modes: meat (28°F), deli (34°F), beverages (39°F), produce (41°F), and party (chill). The drawer has its own sensor, airflow control, and on some SKUs defrost routing. Field reliability has been solid, when service is needed, it's usually sensor drift rather than hardware failure. Our diagnostic reads the Convertible Drawer sensor through the GE service interface, verifies against calibrated probe, replaces if drifted. Sensor service $180–$340. This feature competes directly with Electrolux Perfect Temp and similar full-width convertible drawers on other mid-premium refrigerators."
  },
  {
    q: "What does GE Profile refrigerator repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common GE Profile bands: door gasket (French Door) $200–$380; door gasket (Counter-Depth) $240–$420; Full-Width Freezer Drawer slide service $260–$440; Convertible Drawer sensor or airflow $180–$340; water dispenser fill valve $220–$340; dispenser solenoid $180–$280; ice-maker fill valve + descaling $280–$440; full ice-maker module replacement $420–$620; condenser fan motor $260–$440; evaporator fan $240–$400; defrost heater and thermostat $280–$480; SmartHQ Wi-Fi module replacement $220–$360; main control board $440–$720; variable-speed compressor replacement (post-warranty) $900–$1,500; water filter replacement (homeowner-installable) $40–$80 parts. Parts availability is strong through the GE Appliances US channel, most standard items in-stock or 1-week lead."
  },
  {
    q: "Our GE Profile has an ice-maker that's slow, expected or worth servicing?",
    a: "Slow ice production is one of the most common GE Profile service calls and is almost always worth addressing. Likely causes in order: (1) water filter long overdue for replacement, restricts flow; (2) fill valve mineral buildup from LA hard water, restricts flow; (3) low freezer compartment temperature (check setpoint, 0°F is optimal for ice production, anything warmer slows the ice-mold freeze cycle); (4) ice-maker module itself wearing out at 8–12 years of heavy use. Service order: verify filter age and freezer temperature (5-minute homeowner check), then have us descale the water path and inspect the valve. Full module swap only if the other steps don't restore production. Descale + valve $280–$440; filter refresh by homeowner (free service call, good reminder); module replacement $420–$620 when warranted."
  },
  {
    q: "Should we upgrade from GE Profile to GE Café or Monogram when we renovate?",
    a: "Depends on what you value. We don't sell appliances and don't earn on the upsell, so this is honest feedback based on what our techs see in the field. GE Profile is legitimately good mid-premium refrigeration, for a conventional kitchen where you don't need the built-in flush-with-cabinetry look, Profile does its job well and the ownership cost (initial plus long-term service) is lower than Café or Monogram. Upgrade reasoning that actually makes sense: (1) if the kitchen renovation is contemporary/modernist and you want the Matte Black or Matte White aesthetic with customizable hardware, go Café; (2) if the renovation is full architect-spec built-in with panel-ready cabinetry, go Monogram (or consider Sub-Zero / Miele / Thermador in that tier). Upgrade reasoning that doesn't make sense: \"Profile is basic.\" It isn't, it's a feature-rich mid-premium fridge that genuinely competes with the comparable mid-premium Samsung and Whirlpool models. Keep your money if the aesthetic and architecture aren't driving the decision."
  },
  {
    q: "Are your techs factory-trained on GE Profile specifically?",
    a: "Yes. Our team services the full GE Appliances family, base GE, GE Profile, GE Café, GE Monogram, with platform-specific training across the tiers. GE Profile is one of the highest-volume refrigerator brands in LA (Haier-era investment in GE Appliances has kept GE Profile competitive in the mid-premium market), so our dispatch volume on Profile is substantial and the technical depth is solid. Factory-authorized GE Appliances service runs through GE's own service network and authorized partners, for units still under factory warranty, factory-authorized is the right path. Out of warranty, our independent service with proper Profile training is comparable in quality and typically more responsive on scheduling. We source genuine GE parts through the GE Appliances US channel."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, GE Profile Refrigerator Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical,
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "GE Profile Refrigerator Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "GE Profile refrigerator repair across Southern California, LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Counter-Depth French Door, full-depth French Door, Full-Width Freezer Drawer, Convertible Drawer, Side-by-Side, SmartHQ Wi-Fi integration, water-and-ice dispenser service. GE Appliances mid-premium tier, Haier-owned since 2016, US-manufactured. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": f.q,
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a }
    }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "GE Profile", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/ge-profile/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "GE Profile Refrigerator Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <div class="call-banner">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>GE Profile fridge acting up? Same-day service across LA:</span>
      <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
          <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › GE Profile › Refrigerator Repair</div>
          <h1>GE Profile Refrigerator Repair</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            GE Profile is the feature-focused mid-premium tier of GE Appliances, Counter-Depth French Door,
            Full-Width Freezer Drawer signature, SmartHQ Wi-Fi integration, and Convertible Drawer on current
            models. US-manufactured at Louisville's Appliance Park, Haier-backed since 2016, and one of the
            highest-volume refrigerator brands across our Southern California service area. Our techs service the full Profile lineup across
            LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the
            repair.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
            <a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-facts">
            <li><b>Full-Width Freezer Drawer specialty</b>, slide wear service, alignment protocol</li>
            <li><b>SmartHQ diagnostic</b>, Wi-Fi module, firmware update, router-side troubleshooting</li>
            <li><b>Convertible Drawer service</b>, sensor, airflow, mode-switch diagnostic</li>
            <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
          </ul>
        </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>GE Profile across Southern California, the feature-focused mid-premium choice</h2>
      <p>
        GE Profile sits in the sweet spot of the Southern California refrigerator market: feature-rich enough to
        satisfy a kitchen renovation that wants modern capability (Wi-Fi, Convertible Drawer, Full-Width Freezer
        Drawer, quality water dispenser), priced below the luxury-tier architecture of built-in Monogram or the
        style-focused Café, and with the US-manufactured GE Appliances parts chain backing the product. Most of
        our GE Profile service calls are in mid-premium kitchens across Westside condos, Sherman Oaks and Encino
        family homes, and Pasadena renovations on the LA side; the Newport Beach / Irvine / Tustin Orange County
        belt; the Conejo Valley (Thousand Oaks, Westlake Village, Camarillo); and the Inland Empire premium
        corridor (Rancho Cucamonga, Alta Loma, Temecula wine-country, Murrieta), kitchens where an architect-spec
        built-in wasn't the right fit for the kitchen or the budget.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Haier acquisition of GE Appliances in 2016 has been net-positive for GE Profile. Haier's investment
        has maintained US manufacturing, expanded feature development (SmartHQ platform development, Convertible
        Drawer rollout, refreshed Counter-Depth lineup), and improved parts distribution. For service, that means
        GE Profile parts are broadly available through the GE Appliances US channel with strong supply depth ,
        one of the reasons Profile service economics are competitive compared to mid-premium alternatives.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>GE Profile refrigerator failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Pattern data from our GE Profile coverage. Six clusters cover most dispatch. Profile runs a high-volume
        residential refrigerator platform, so the field-data set is mature and the failure patterns are well-
        understood.
      </p>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Slow ice production, filter, valve, or freezer temp</h3>
        <p>
          Most common GE Profile service call. Cause chain: overdue water filter (restricts flow), scaled fill
          valve (hard-water districts across our service area, particularly the IE), freezer compartment set too warm (slows mold freeze cycle), or aged ice-
          maker module. Homeowner can verify filter + freezer setpoint before we roll; descale + valve service
          $280–$440; module replacement $420–$620 if warranted.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Water dispenser no flow or low pressure</h3>
        <p>
          Test inlet pressure, inspect filter, verify fill-valve operation, check dispenser solenoid. Fill-valve
          replacement $220–$340. Dispenser solenoid $180–$280. Filter replacement (homeowner-installable) $40–$80
          parts, no service call needed unless housing is damaged or electronics fault.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Full-Width Freezer Drawer slide wear at 6–10 years</h3>
        <p>
          The heavy single-width freezer drawer carries more load than split twin-drawer designs, and the slide
          hardware wears at 6–10 years of daily use. Symptom: drawer sticks, doesn't close flush, or rolls unevenly.
          Slide-rail replacement with alignment verification $260–$440.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>SmartHQ Wi-Fi association / notification issues</h3>
        <p>
          Wi-Fi drops, notifications stop delivering, or app shows appliance offline. Router-side issue first
          (home Wi-Fi strength and interference), then GE-side firmware update, finally Wi-Fi module replacement.
          Most cases resolve at firmware level. Firmware update $120–$180; Wi-Fi module $220–$360.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Convertible Drawer sensor drift</h3>
        <p>
          Convertible Drawer produces temperature misread in a specific mode, meat mode running too warm,
          beverages mode too cold. Usually sensor drift, occasionally airflow-baffle frost. Sensor replacement
          $180–$340.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Compressor start / run capacitor at 10–14 years</h3>
        <p>
          Variable-speed compressor on the Profile platform is generally reliable 10–14 years; when service is
          needed at this age, capacitor or starter relay is the common fault before the compressor itself. Meter
          the capacitor, verify compressor health, swap if bad. $180–$280. Actual post-warranty compressor
          replacement $900–$1,500, uncommon before year 12.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>GE Profile US refrigerator lines we service</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        GE Profile refrigeration spans French Door, Counter-Depth French Door, Side-by-Side, Top-Freezer, and
        select built-in-style configurations. PWE, PFE, PVD model number prefixes identify the Profile tier.
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Counter-Depth French Door (PWE prefix)</h3>
          <p>The most common Profile install across our service area. 36-inch and 33-inch widths, counter-depth profile (sits flush with
          cabinets), Full-Width Freezer Drawer bottom, French Door upper, in-door water/ice dispenser on select
          SKUs, SmartHQ Wi-Fi.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Full-Depth French Door (PFE prefix)</h3>
          <p>Deeper traditional French Door with larger internal capacity. Same feature set as Counter-Depth but
          with conventional body depth. Good value for larger entertaining kitchens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Side-by-Side (PZS prefix)</h3>
          <p>Profile Side-by-Side with in-door ice and water dispenser. Slightly older architecture in the Profile
          lineup; French Door has taken most of the market share, but Side-by-Side still serves clients who prefer
          the layout.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>4-Door French Door</h3>
          <p>French Door upper plus twin-drawer lower (fridge-drawer + freezer-drawer) for greater compartment
          flexibility. Convertible Drawer typically lives in this configuration. Premium within the Profile tier.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Convertible Drawer (signature feature)</h3>
          <p>Full-width drawer with 5-mode switching: meat, deli, beverages, produce, party-chill. Electronic
          control via SmartHQ or in-door display. Common on 4-Door and certain Counter-Depth Profile SKUs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>SmartHQ Wi-Fi integration</h3>
          <p>GE Appliances' ecosystem Wi-Fi platform. Status monitoring, setpoint adjustment, alerts, OTA firmware.
          Shared across Profile, Café, and Monogram tiers. Service-side: firmware-first diagnostic approach.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>GE Profile vs the mid-premium competition, the honest field read</h2>
      <p>
        GE Profile's peer tier includes Samsung premium French Door, LG premium French Door, Bosch 500/800 Series,
        KitchenAid, and Electrolux. Our techs service the whole tier. Here's the honest positioning.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Samsung</b>, Strong Family Hub and Bespoke innovations; some 2020-era Samsung units had documented
        compressor and ice-maker issues that affected reliability. See
        <a href="/brands/samsung-refrigerator-repair/">Samsung refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>LG</b>, Linear Compressor technology, InstaView Door-in-Door innovation; the 2014–2017 Linear
        Compressor class-action issue affected this generation. See
        <a href="/brands/lg-refrigerator-repair/">LG refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Electrolux</b>, Swedish parent, Frigidaire platform sharing, Perfect Temp full-width drawer. See
        <a href="/brands/electrolux-refrigerator-repair/">Electrolux refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>GE Profile</b>, US-manufactured, Haier-backed, SmartHQ + Convertible Drawer + Full-Width Freezer Drawer
        feature set, strong parts availability. Best pick when the household wants reliable mid-premium performance
        from a US-made product with a broadly-available parts chain, without the risk profile of some Samsung/LG
        generations and without the boutique-Italian parts lead times. Cross-link sibling tiers:
        <a href="/brands/ge-cafe-refrigerator-repair/">GE Café</a>, <a href="/brands/ge-monogram-refrigerator-repair/">GE
        Monogram</a>, and base <a href="/brands/ge-refrigerator-repair/">GE</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>What GE Profile refrigerator repair costs in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">Parts pricing is competitive within the mid-premium tier; GE Appliances' US parts channel
      means strong availability and reasonable lead times. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Flat, waived if repair is authorized same visit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (French Door)</td><td>$200 – $380</td><td>Standard French Door profile</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (Counter-Depth)</td><td>$240 – $420</td><td>Tighter reveal on counter-depth</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Full-Width Freezer Drawer slide service</td><td>$260 – $440</td><td>6–10 year wear pattern</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Convertible Drawer sensor or airflow</td><td>$180 – $340</td><td>Mode-specific temperature misread</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Water dispenser fill valve</td><td>$220 – $340</td><td>Hard-water SoCal districts (esp. IE)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Dispenser solenoid replacement</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>No-flow dispenser symptom</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ice-maker fill valve + descaling</td><td>$280 – $440</td><td>Hard-water households</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ice-maker module replacement</td><td>$420 – $620</td><td>Slow-ice final resolution</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor capacitor / starter relay</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>10–14 year unit common service</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser fan motor replacement</td><td>$260 – $440</td><td>Standard Profile specs on truck</td></tr>
        <tr><td>SmartHQ firmware update</td><td>$120 – $180</td><td>Most Wi-Fi issues resolve at firmware</td></tr>
        <tr><td>SmartHQ Wi-Fi module replacement</td><td>$220 – $360</td><td>Firmware-resistant cases</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Main control board replacement</td><td>$440 – $720</td><td>Post-firmware diagnosis</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Variable-speed compressor (post-warranty)</td><td>$900 – $1,500</td><td>Uncommon before year 12</td></tr>
      </table>
      <p class="small">
        Broader refrigerator cost reference: our <a href="/price-list/refrigerator-repair-cost/">refrigerator repair
        cost guide</a>. Service hub: <a href="/services/refrigerator-repair/">refrigerator repair</a>. GE Profile
        range, cooktop, and wall oven repair covered on sibling pages, see the GE Profile
        <a href="/brands/ge-profile/">brand hub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Service areas, where our GE Profile calls come from</h2>
      <div class="area-grid">
        <div>
          <h4>San Fernando Valley (mainstream families)</h4>
          <p><a href="/encino/">Encino</a> · Sherman Oaks · Tarzana · Woodland Hills · Studio City · North Hollywood</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Westside (mid-premium condos + homes)</h4>
          <p><a href="/beverly-hills/">Beverly Hills</a> · <a href="/brentwood/">Brentwood</a> · <a href="/santa-monica/">Santa Monica</a> · <a href="/west-hollywood/">West Hollywood</a></p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>San Gabriel Valley</h4>
          <p><a href="/pasadena/">Pasadena</a> · San Marino · Glendale · Burbank · South Pasadena · La Cañada</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Coastal</h4>
          <p><a href="/malibu/">Malibu</a> · Venice · Marina del Rey · Manhattan Beach · Redondo Beach</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>South Bay + Downtown</h4>
          <p>Torrance · Palos Verdes · Downtown LA · Koreatown · Hollywood</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Orange County premium</h4>
          <p>Newport Beach · <a href="/irvine/">Irvine</a> · Laguna Beach · Corona del Mar · Tustin · Anaheim Hills</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Ventura + Conejo Valley</h4>
          <p><a href="/thousand-oaks/">Thousand Oaks</a> · Westlake Village · Hidden Hills · Camarillo · Simi Valley</p>
